01:45:55,299 --> 01:45:59,880
I am curious how it got licensed, how it got permits to open up.

1305
01:46:00,901 --> 01:46:04,822
I'm curious how it's going to affect the other businesses in Medford Square.

1306
01:46:04,842 --> 01:46:10,424
In addition to my role with the MCC, I'm also the programming coordinator for Circle the Square.

1307
01:46:11,357 --> 01:46:17,718
And as, hopefully, if you've been to Circle the Square before, hundreds of people come to Medford Square, many of them families.

1308
01:46:18,299 --> 01:46:20,739
Riverside Avenue is a huge destination.

1309
01:46:21,199 --> 01:46:33,822
We have a ton of programming at Burying Ground, and now hundreds of people, including many families, are going to be walking past this particular establishment at 34 Riverside Avenue, which, at the very least, is sketchy.

1310
01:46:34,896 --> 01:46:51,965
I'm also curious, of course, in the larger picture of things, if this is a human trafficking situation, that obviously is a very serious issue, one that we can't necessarily completely solve within Medford City Council, but this is obviously the larger issue at hand.

1311
01:46:52,926 --> 01:46:59,529
And I'm also curious what can be done to keep these businesses from coming back

1312
01:47:00,225 --> 01:47:12,991
In doing a little bit of research, it seems like some of our neighbors and surrounding communities have changed their ordinances within their towns to not only prevent these types of businesses from coming in the first place or to severely restrict them.

1313
01:47:13,551 --> 01:47:25,237
And so I think that Medford should take those same kinds of steps so that we don't have to continually, as you mentioned, year after year or every couple of years have to sort of readdress this situation.

1314
01:47:25,657 --> 01:47:27,018
It sounds like it can be done.

1315
01:47:27,767 --> 01:47:33,152
within each town and community that there can be changes made to prevent these from opening.

1316
01:47:33,553 --> 01:47:33,893
Thank you.

1317
01:47:36,676 --> 01:47:38,618
Frank O'Leary, 85 Arlington Street.

1318
01:47:38,638 --> 01:47:41,140
I'm also on the board of the MCC.

1319
01:47:41,580 --> 01:47:43,342
Just have a basic statement.

1320
01:47:43,382 --> 01:47:48,147
The Medford, as I see it, is beginning a huge transition period.

1321
01:47:48,908 --> 01:47:50,269
We're on a border where

1322
01:47:51,093 --> 01:48:05,497
We can go one way or the other way by allowing businesses in that foster a wrong idea, make the square itself feel unsafe in the evening for families to come walking through.

1323
01:48:06,318 --> 01:48:07,858
Recently, the square has been decimated.

1324
01:48:08,979 --> 01:48:10,339
We're losing valuable businesses.

1325
01:48:11,119 --> 01:48:17,061
Everybody talks about how we want the square to be a place for people to come and enjoy themselves in the evenings.

1326
01:48:18,121 --> 01:48:20,002
They're not going to do that if they have to worry about

1327
01:48:20,737 --> 01:48:22,477
you know, the type of businesses that are coming in.

1328
01:48:22,497 --> 01:48:32,339
You know, if there's things that can be done, permits that need to be viewed, or even just in general, look at Elements Massage.

1329
01:48:32,939 --> 01:48:34,380
It's a reputable place.

1330
01:48:35,400 --> 01:48:37,700
Those people are certified, individually trained.

1331
01:48:37,780 --> 01:48:42,601
They spend years doing this type of stuff.

1332
01:48:44,022 --> 01:48:45,162
What message do you want to send?

1333
01:48:47,054 --> 01:48:52,998
Anybody come in who's going to have, who can put up a shingle or we appreciate accreditation.

1334
01:48:53,698 --> 01:48:56,160
We appreciate businesses that are going to give back to the community.

1335
01:48:56,180 --> 01:48:59,702
They're going to foster the right image that we want to present.

1336
01:49:01,443 --> 01:49:04,985
Now it's, it's, it's not just the council, it's everybody.

1337
01:49:05,166 --> 01:49:06,286
Citizens need to pay attention.

1338
01:49:07,107 --> 01:49:08,328
Everybody needs to be a part of this.

1339
01:49:08,668 --> 01:49:09,468
We're together in this.

1340
01:49:10,849 --> 01:49:11,109
Thank you.

1341
01:49:11,590 --> 01:49:11,910
Thank you.

1342
01:49:23,382 --> 01:49:25,163
Mark Crowley, 59 Boynton Road.

1343
01:49:26,764 --> 01:49:30,686
I've got to have to say, you know, congrats to the MCC for really making a lot of this happen.

1344
01:49:30,706 --> 01:49:32,087
I really appreciate that.

1345
01:49:32,647 --> 01:49:38,350
And, you know, I think it's unfortunate that, you know, the notion of being reactive is exactly what we hear a lot.

1346
01:49:39,190 --> 01:49:42,031
And unfortunately, it's, you know, you sow what you reap in many ways.

1347
01:49:42,091 --> 01:49:48,795
And that, you know, the efforts by the city towards economic development in our business districts, you know, has been completely inadequate.

1348
01:49:48,815 --> 01:49:51,056
And, you know, certainly today we're going to be talking about Medford Square.

1349
01:49:51,423 --> 01:49:56,885
But, I mean, this is a problem that we see across the city, you know, whether it be the vacant storefronts on Salem Street or anywhere else.

1350
01:49:56,905 --> 01:50:00,727
You know, you look at the roads or anywhere in Boston Ave, Winthrop Street, or around the Hillside area.

1351
01:50:00,747 --> 01:50:09,350
You know, if you're not trying to attract, as Councilor Marks alluded to, and support those desirable businesses, you're going to get the less than desirable ones.

1352
01:50:10,371 --> 01:50:11,811
It's like maintaining your front lawn.

1353
01:50:12,011 --> 01:50:15,793
If you don't water, you don't fertilize, you don't care for it, you're going to get weeds.

1354
01:50:16,073 --> 01:50:16,773
And that's what we're getting.

1355
01:50:17,033 --> 01:50:18,434
We're getting weeds in Medford Square.

1356
01:50:19,293 --> 01:50:23,336
We need City Hall to be at the forefront of attracting new businesses.

1357
01:50:23,676 --> 01:50:27,559
And sure, we can say, gosh, you know, the Office of Community Development, you know, doesn't have enough resources.

1358
01:50:27,619 --> 01:50:28,079
That's true.

1359
01:50:28,620 --> 01:50:29,881
The city can find resources.

1360
01:50:29,901 --> 01:50:32,242
We've got a $155 million budget.

1361
01:50:32,543 --> 01:50:38,767
The mayor miraculously found $250,000, much to his, you know, applause, to fund the, you know, the library.

1362
01:50:39,067 --> 01:50:45,232
But why aren't we making the investments at something that actually will generate additional tax revenues for this city?

1363
01:50:45,632 --> 01:50:46,973
Where is that investment being made?

1364
01:50:47,772 --> 01:50:49,213
And this isn't a new problem.

1365
01:50:49,513 --> 01:50:53,874
This isn't something that, you know, we just woke up and say, oh, gosh, look, there's empty storefronts in Medford Square.

1366
01:50:54,335 --> 01:51:00,757
Or, you know, now we've got a pawn shop, and it is a pawn shop right next to a questionable salon.

1367
01:51:02,778 --> 01:51:08,240
Back in 2004, there was an effort, a Medford Square master plan.

1368
01:51:09,040 --> 01:51:10,241
It's a great document.

1369
01:51:10,481 --> 01:51:13,382
I remember attending a lot of public hearings and listening to things about it.

1370
01:51:14,162 --> 01:51:15,583
Lots of really great ideas in there.

1371
01:51:16,057 --> 01:51:18,579
Unfortunately, it seems no one in this building has actually read it.

1372
01:51:19,240 --> 01:51:21,882
Because the challenge is, it's a beautiful document.

1373
01:51:22,623 --> 01:51:23,664
It's got a blueprint.

1374
01:51:23,784 --> 01:51:26,466
It tells this city what it should be doing.

1375
01:51:27,407 --> 01:51:28,888
Put a marketing plan in place.

1376
01:51:29,449 --> 01:51:32,191
Start investing in these abandoned lots that are parking lots.

1377
01:51:32,615 --> 01:51:41,863
You turn those into private development, build new buildings here, start to incite and be that catalyst for this eastern side of the square.

1378
01:51:42,543 --> 01:52:01,739
Put in facade improvements and other ordinances that mandate and even support and even help maybe provide tax incentives or even low-interest loans so that buildings along Riverside and Salem Street can make the investments necessary to replace the chipping paint, to replace the torn awnings, to replace the chipping concrete in each of those buildings.

1379
01:52:02,062 --> 01:52:04,085
No reputable business wants to come into those spaces.

1380
01:52:04,706 --> 01:52:15,620
I congratulate and I applaud folks like Mystic Coffee Roasters and Carroll's and Tinosh and Salvatore's and unfortunately, as of recently, Best Sellers, but these guys can't do it on their own.

1381
01:52:16,140 --> 01:52:17,322
They need this city.

1382
01:52:17,738 --> 01:52:21,401
to make the investments and make the priority decisions that need to be done.

1383
01:52:21,421 --> 01:52:23,323
You know, other cities are doing it.

1384
01:52:23,383 --> 01:52:24,203
Boston has it.

1385
01:52:24,624 --> 01:52:25,424
Cambridge has it.

1386
01:52:25,505 --> 01:52:26,225
Somerville has it.

1387
01:52:26,265 --> 01:52:27,626
God, even Malden has it.

1388
01:52:27,666 --> 01:52:31,450
And God forbid we compare ourselves to Malden, but they've got a redevelopment authority.

1389
01:52:31,870 --> 01:52:32,751
Where is Medford?

1390
01:52:33,011 --> 01:52:34,352
Where's our marketing plan?

1391
01:52:34,812 --> 01:52:36,594
Why aren't we out there banging on the trees?

1392
01:52:36,634 --> 01:52:37,655
Where's the mayor talking?

1393
01:52:37,675 --> 01:52:41,958
You know, sure, maybe Office of Community Development can't do it by themselves, but there's a lot of other people in this building.

1394
01:52:41,978 --> 01:52:43,039
Where's the Chamber of Commerce?

1395
01:52:43,279 --> 01:52:46,222
Who's out there trying to advocate for the city of Medford?

1396
01:52:46,710 --> 01:52:56,377
Why does it have to be citizen groups like the Medford Community Coalition and CASH that are holding cash mobs and cleanups and concerts and street fairs trying to breathe life back into the square?

1397
01:52:56,717 --> 01:52:59,459
It needs to be this building that leads the charge.

1398
01:52:59,999 --> 01:53:04,742
And let's not think that, you know, businesses aren't just simply about, you know, profits and business owners.

1399
01:53:05,142 --> 01:53:11,807
They're about, as we're starting to see here with respect to the pawn shop and the spa, they're about public safety.

1400
01:53:12,188 --> 01:53:17,072
But they're also about generating diversity in terms of reflecting the diverse needs of the city.

1401
01:53:17,333 --> 01:53:18,514
They generate tax dollars.

1402
01:53:18,994 --> 01:53:22,477
They improve the opportunities to invest in other things.

1403
01:53:22,718 --> 01:53:24,099
They bring jobs to our neighbors.

1404
01:53:25,320 --> 01:53:27,482
It's time the city gets serious about economic development.

1405
01:53:27,502 --> 01:53:29,944
We've been talking about it for years and years and years.

1406
01:53:30,264 --> 01:53:31,065
We've got a plan.

1407
01:53:31,305 --> 01:53:32,046
We've got the ideas.

1408
01:53:32,086 --> 01:53:35,309
We just need people to actually start doing their jobs and make it happen.

1409
01:53:35,830 --> 01:53:36,130
Thank you.

1410
01:53:42,245 --> 01:53:44,166
Hi, please state your name and address for the record.

1411
01:53:45,006 --> 01:53:47,887
Yes, Margaret Weigel, 64 Forest Street.

1412
01:53:49,268 --> 01:53:52,910
And so I would like to say that I've heard a lot about these businesses.

1413
01:53:53,190 --> 01:53:53,790
I'm really tall.

1414
01:53:54,771 --> 01:53:57,272
Coming into quote, unquote, residential areas.

1415
01:53:59,493 --> 01:53:59,733
Really?

1416
01:54:00,073 --> 01:54:00,693
Can you hear me now?

1417
01:54:01,493 --> 01:54:02,074
OK, good.

1418
01:54:02,214 --> 01:54:02,554
Great.

1419
01:54:04,195 --> 01:54:08,517
So talking about it coming into residential areas, but Medford Square is my backyard.

1420
01:54:08,577 --> 01:54:09,537
This is where I live.

1421
01:54:09,677 --> 01:54:11,738
This is where I get off the bus to walk to home.

1422
01:54:12,404 --> 01:54:17,996
I walk off the bus sometimes at 8 o'clock and everything is closed except Asian Body Works.

1423
01:54:18,457 --> 01:54:22,265
It's become a very different place in recent weeks since it opened.

1424
01:54:23,437 --> 01:54:31,660
I'd like to reiterate the comments that I've heard from my citizens about being a little bit more proactive about the kind of businesses that come into the square.

1425
01:54:31,680 --> 01:54:42,444
I think Medford has adopted either accidentally or just by default a program of benign neglect in terms of the business development, and I think it's one of those things.

1426
01:54:42,524 --> 01:54:49,447
I know money is hard to come by and nobody wants to spend the money, but it's the kind of investment that will be paid back tenfold once

1427
01:54:49,968 --> 01:54:53,990
it's implemented, it will attract new revenue, it will attract other attractive businesses.

1428
01:54:54,890 --> 01:55:01,213
Medford will be the place that people choose to come to instead of being the default city because they are priced out of other communities.

1429
01:55:03,073 --> 01:55:11,177
I think other people have said everything that I want to say, but I did want to reiterate that Medford Square is home to a lot of people too.

1430
01:55:11,497 --> 01:55:12,257
That's all, thank you.

1431
01:55:16,459 --> 01:55:18,480
Hi, please state your name and address for the record.

1432
01:55:19,880 --> 01:55:28,106
Hi, I'm Sharon Hepburn, 228 Governors Avenue, and also owner of Mystic Coffee Roaster at 30 Riverside Avenue, just two doors down from the new establishment.

1433
01:55:29,808 --> 01:55:32,110
I want to echo what has already been said.

1434
01:55:32,790 --> 01:55:35,152
This is the result of no city planning.

1435
01:55:36,293 --> 01:55:38,895
We really need a strong community development office.

1436
01:55:39,315 --> 01:55:41,177
We need you guys to all work together.

1437
01:55:41,197 --> 01:55:45,840
The city does need to be leading the charge on this.

1438
01:55:46,721 --> 01:55:49,283
And we as a community are trying to come together,

1439
01:55:49,750 --> 01:55:54,473
to do something about it, but we can't do it all, and you guys need to help us.

1440
01:55:55,734 --> 01:55:59,597
And whoever's running for mayor needs to be listening, because you guys are on notice.

1441
01:56:00,458 --> 01:56:02,179
We're watching, all right?

1442
01:56:04,200 --> 01:56:15,168
I would also like to explore maybe the idea of if anything illegal is happening in these places, are landlords culpable for the illegal activity going on?

1443
01:56:16,739 --> 01:56:20,783
I really think the city needs to work with the landlords in the square.

1444
01:56:20,803 --> 01:56:28,752
A lot of places are going out of business because the rents are being jacked up, and we have empty storefronts.

1445
01:56:32,088 --> 01:56:35,551
is working to bring in new businesses.

1446
01:56:35,951 --> 01:56:45,439
And I have to tell you, I have been approached by other community development offices from other cities to locate in other cities.

1447
01:56:45,479 --> 01:56:46,420
But this is my city.

1448
01:56:46,460 --> 01:56:47,321
I want to be here.

1449
01:56:48,381 --> 01:56:55,868
And like I said, we really need the city to be leading the charge on this.

1450
01:56:56,988 --> 01:56:57,309
Thank you.

1451
01:56:57,729 --> 01:56:58,510
Thank you very much.

1452
01:57:02,045 --> 01:57:03,926
Hi, please state your name and address for the record.

1453
01:57:04,306 --> 01:57:05,346
Hi, my name is Jay Campbell.

1454
01:57:05,386 --> 01:57:07,087
I live at 707 Fulton Street.

1455
01:57:07,247 --> 01:57:08,927
I'm really just myself a resident.

1456
01:57:08,987 --> 01:57:13,549
So I just want to give my two cents on the whole thing with the massage parlors and everything else.

1457
01:57:14,469 --> 01:57:15,710
I think it's great that you brought it up.

1458
01:57:15,970 --> 01:57:16,990
I think it's a great point.

1459
01:57:17,390 --> 01:57:22,632
I also think that a lot of people don't realize that you cannot legally tell a business not to come into the city.

1460
01:57:23,212 --> 01:57:25,033
But what you can do is create zoning.

1461
01:57:25,650 --> 01:57:27,251
And I think that's something that MedFed lacks.

1462
01:57:27,311 --> 01:57:36,834
Right now, myself, any of you, anyone here, could open up a strip club next to Bistro 5, because it's a legal business and you can.

1463
01:57:37,414 --> 01:57:44,036
What you do need is adult zoning in the city of MedFed.

1464
01:57:44,056 --> 01:57:45,657
I haven't seen, oh, I was talking to other people.

1465
01:57:45,677 --> 01:57:47,217
Point of information, Councilor Pinto.

1466
01:57:47,717 --> 01:57:48,358
You do have that?

1467
01:57:48,678 --> 01:57:48,898
Yes.

1468
01:57:49,858 --> 01:57:52,779
You made a comment about next to Bistro 5, you could put a strip joint.

1469
01:57:53,132 --> 01:57:55,194
City of Meffitt has what they call an entertainment zone.

1470
01:57:55,214 --> 01:57:57,797
There's only one spot in the city and that's on the end of Mystic Avenue.

1471
01:57:58,117 --> 01:57:59,819
That's the only place that something like that.

1472
01:57:59,839 --> 01:58:00,400
That's great.

1473
01:58:00,420 --> 01:58:01,721
So I was on the stand that we didn't have it.

1474
01:58:01,761 --> 01:58:02,602
So that's fantastic.

1475
01:58:02,642 --> 01:58:07,648
And it would be great if we could maybe take that and add some of these other businesses that might be cropping up.

1476
01:58:08,151 --> 01:58:10,373
into that same category, like zone it that way.

1477
01:58:11,473 --> 01:58:13,915
So that way you don't have this issue.

1478
01:58:13,955 --> 01:58:20,539
Because you can't say to somebody, we think you're sketchy, we don't really want you here, but you don't really know.

1479
01:58:21,480 --> 01:58:24,602
And the other thing is, chief, if you need someone for social media, give me a call.

1480
01:58:25,282 --> 01:58:25,943
I'll be happy to help.

1481
01:58:26,623 --> 01:58:27,704
But I just want to bring that up.

1482
01:58:27,744 --> 01:58:31,186
I'm glad to know that Medford does have that zoning, because I wasn't aware of that.

1483
01:58:31,346 --> 01:58:31,867
So that's great.

1484
01:58:31,987 --> 01:58:32,447
So thank you.

1485
01:58:32,707 --> 01:58:33,047
Thank you.

1486
01:58:38,854 --> 01:58:46,760
Mr. President, I haven't changed my address, so do I necessarily need to give my name and address?

1487
01:58:48,402 --> 01:58:57,329
I'm probably the only person here that's going to ask some interesting and technical questions.

1488
01:58:59,791 --> 01:59:03,435
Excuse me, but this is ringing in my ears, and I can't hear it.

1489
01:59:04,251 --> 01:59:06,712
I'm trying to do two things at once with it.

1490
01:59:07,232 --> 01:59:12,353
One, hear from it, and the other one, make sure it doesn't ring in your microphones.

1491
01:59:13,273 --> 01:59:15,973
Number one, the gentleman before me is right.

1492
01:59:16,153 --> 01:59:20,914
You can't actually not let some businesses in.

1493
01:59:21,335 --> 01:59:25,976
Now, I've been hearing it as a pawn shop, the business.

1494
01:59:26,336 --> 01:59:32,037
Well, you'll have to excuse me, but the pawn shop

1495
01:59:33,667 --> 01:59:37,869
TV show is one of the most popular TV shows in the United States.

1496
01:59:38,509 --> 01:59:44,812
It keeps a station on cable TV.

1497
01:59:45,813 --> 01:59:52,076
Hence, there are probably as equal many people out here on the pawn shop.

1498
01:59:52,376 --> 01:59:58,439
I've never been invited to the circle of the square things, nor somebody my age.

1499
01:59:59,418 --> 02:00:02,020
probably, or have been too often.

1500
02:00:03,161 --> 02:00:13,309
Two, there are more 50-year-olds in the city than there are under 50 who do the voting.

1501
02:00:14,790 --> 02:00:15,611
How do I know that?

1502
02:00:15,631 --> 02:00:22,176
Because as at least several of you have worked on your campaigns, and we've proven that.

1503
02:00:25,130 --> 02:00:31,231
The other thing is, the pawn shop is a secondary market for products.

1504
02:00:32,751 --> 02:00:39,072
Just like Morgan Memorial, just like Salvation Army.

1505
02:00:39,813 --> 02:00:46,434
Now when I got out of the Army, the Salvation Army and the Red Cross helped me with my disabilities.

1506
02:00:47,574 --> 02:00:52,735
And when I got out of the Army, and that was in the 60s by the way, I'm an old man now,

1507
02:00:53,668 --> 02:01:01,155
The only one that pawn shop type business that helped me was the Salvation Army.

1508
02:01:02,677 --> 02:01:08,082
Now, I've bought clothes and products in the so-called pawn shop.

1509
02:01:08,142 --> 02:01:09,443
I didn't know it was a pawn shop.

1510
02:01:09,723 --> 02:01:11,265
I thought it was a secondary shop.

1511
02:01:12,686 --> 02:01:17,451
And I don't think it has a pawn shop license, so I wouldn't call it a pawn shop.

1512
02:01:19,516 --> 02:01:27,298
I think what you're doing is saying we want the square and the people in the square for one group of people.

1513
02:01:28,218 --> 02:01:30,959
By the way, I also made Medford my home.

1514
02:01:33,360 --> 02:01:37,361
I didn't come here because it was a dirty, rotten place.

1515
02:01:37,721 --> 02:01:38,921
I thought it was quite good.

