02:49:45,669 --> 02:49:45,869
Thank you.

2154
02:49:45,889 --> 02:49:46,550
Thank you, Ms.

2155
02:49:46,590 --> 02:49:46,810
Miller.

2156
02:49:47,170 --> 02:49:49,551
If I could just request whatever you're provided by the

2157
02:49:50,782 --> 02:49:56,987
fire union, if you could forward that to us so we can get an idea, because I remember a couple more things on that list.

2158
02:49:57,387 --> 02:50:01,730
Whether it was air conditioning and heating is still an issue at one or two of the fire stations as well.

2159
02:50:01,750 --> 02:50:03,771
I remember that being another problem.

2160
02:50:03,852 --> 02:50:09,275
So if we could get that list from the fire union as well.

2161
02:50:09,315 --> 02:50:09,676
Thank you.

2162
02:50:11,297 --> 02:50:12,118
Councillor Pente.

2163
02:50:13,038 --> 02:50:13,719
A few questions.

2164
02:50:14,519 --> 02:50:18,262
Louise, one of the things that we had asked for was our electrical department.

2165
02:50:19,112 --> 02:50:24,615
that the superintendent wise, um, contact national grid to address the lack of lighting at Wentworth street rotary.

2166
02:50:25,596 --> 02:50:32,540
The response is that the lack of lighting is due to the removal of one street light for construction reasons and will be reinstalled.

2167
02:50:33,281 --> 02:50:37,904
The other answer was one street light was struck by a truck and has been struck on more than one occasion.

2168
02:50:37,964 --> 02:50:42,687
National grid is evaluating, evaluating whether or not to reinstall due to this location.

2169
02:50:43,527 --> 02:50:45,428
Now, have you ever gone to Wentworth circle at nighttime?

2170
02:50:46,809 --> 02:50:47,430
I have not.

2171
02:50:47,750 --> 02:50:48,030
Okay.

2172
02:50:48,711 --> 02:50:53,515
Well, if you go there at nighttime, you think you're in the woods, because there's absolutely no lights.

2173
02:50:53,775 --> 02:50:54,856
It's as dark as can be.

2174
02:50:55,837 --> 02:50:57,338
It's a huge public safety issue.

2175
02:50:58,559 --> 02:51:05,324
We had asked Mr. Randazzo for whatever it takes to put additional lighting in there while this whole construction is going on.

2176
02:51:06,085 --> 02:51:10,428
Now, I know that they're repaving part of the street in Winthrop Street, but they're still working over there.

2177
02:51:11,429 --> 02:51:17,694
And to have National Grid tell us that they're going to evaluate whether, in fact, they're going to put a new light up, that doesn't make any sense.

2178
02:51:18,632 --> 02:51:23,055
And that's the type of an answer I would have not responded to by saying that.

2179
02:51:23,396 --> 02:51:26,558
I would have went out of my way to make sure national grid did put the light up there.

2180
02:51:26,618 --> 02:51:27,759
It's a public safety issue.

2181
02:51:28,139 --> 02:51:31,002
It's a huge factor over there and that needs to be addressed.

2182
02:51:32,843 --> 02:51:39,548
Also, there's some concerns that I had in this budget from four particular departments, engineering, the library, the building and the police department.

2183
02:51:40,329 --> 02:51:44,572
And I think we were all educated, at least I was immensely during this past budgetary process,

2184
02:51:45,208 --> 02:51:59,791
that these four departments in particular, when asked about their wish list, for which we've been asking each and every year, well, judges knew, as you're aware now, they were all very enlightening to turn around and tell us that they did ask for certain things.

2185
02:52:00,311 --> 02:52:13,773
The engineering department in particular, when the engineering director was asked what her wish list was, and she had been asking for this for four years, and how was it done, two times it was verbal,

2186
02:52:14,864 --> 02:52:22,386
And two times it was in an email, and she was told by her predecessor not to include it in the budget, because you weren't going to get it.

2187
02:52:22,986 --> 02:52:28,327
Well, how do you deny having four people use one telephone call, one telephone?

2188
02:52:28,727 --> 02:52:38,229
How do you deny giving them an extra table to work on, file cabinets, and a computerization system to bring them up to date, or at least to keep them up to date, for a $30,000 to a $40,000 hit?

2189
02:52:38,249 --> 02:52:38,670
I don't know.

2190
02:52:41,757 --> 02:52:45,119
Paul Mulkey from the building department, when he came up, he was asking for something very simple.

2191
02:52:45,579 --> 02:52:48,221
He wanted to become modernized and more computerized.

2192
02:52:49,142 --> 02:52:51,263
And that was costing him maybe $30,000 to $40,000, asking.

2193
02:52:51,423 --> 02:52:55,566
Is the chief still here?

2194
02:52:55,626 --> 02:52:56,707
I don't want to put him on the spot.

2195
02:52:56,767 --> 02:52:59,909
But the question was asked of the chief relative to his wish list.

2196
02:53:00,409 --> 02:53:01,269
He had never been asked.

2197
02:53:01,790 --> 02:53:07,854
And when it was asked of you on the night of the budget, you indicated that you had just heard it that morning from the chief.

2198
02:53:08,814 --> 02:53:09,855
And here is the department.

2199
02:53:10,258 --> 02:53:18,383
that has cars and a building and a whole gamut of issues still not being addressed.

2200
02:53:19,364 --> 02:53:27,109
The library, for four years, the poor librarian, and including myself, have been all over him because he's not putting these things into the budget.

2201
02:53:27,689 --> 02:53:37,415
And it took a cast of characters from our community to say that they wanted that library fixed and they wanted their recertification to come forward.

2202
02:53:39,256 --> 02:53:39,997
And what had happened?

2203
02:53:40,937 --> 02:53:48,341
When Mr. Bryan was there, he was told not to say anything and not to put in his library by your predecessor.

2204
02:53:49,301 --> 02:53:51,322
For six years, we went without being certified.

2205
02:53:51,743 --> 02:53:55,084
We kept getting these variances and these special privileges from the state.

2206
02:53:55,845 --> 02:54:06,870
That, to me, did not represent what a true budget is all about, because that $225,000, $30,000, or whatever it should have been, should have been part of the daily operating budget that that department needs to have.

2207
02:54:08,211 --> 02:54:10,332
And then lastly, I think the question was asked to you.

2208
02:54:10,806 --> 02:54:14,829
And I don't think I was the one that asked the question, but I believe the question was asked to you.

2209
02:54:15,329 --> 02:54:19,333
Would you have presented the budget the same way you got it to be presented?

2210
02:54:19,913 --> 02:54:22,035
And you said no, you would have presented it different.

2211
02:54:22,495 --> 02:54:30,921
Because I think you heard about our wish list, a page that had about expensive, a page about salaries, and a page about the whole operation.

2212
02:54:31,302 --> 02:54:32,403
To me, that spoke volumes.

2213
02:54:33,403 --> 02:54:35,265
Taking a quick look over to the school department,

2214
02:54:37,948 --> 02:54:43,869
whether Roy wants to agree with me or not, for whatever it might be, we had a conversation about the Curtis Tufts School.

2215
02:54:44,589 --> 02:54:48,550
Now, the Curtis Tufts School, to some degree, has been a little bit of a bone of contention.

2216
02:54:49,030 --> 02:54:54,611
But our own superintendent at that meeting indicated they had to make some changes because it wasn't going in the right direction.

2217
02:54:54,971 --> 02:54:57,571
You can correct me if the words are wrong, but I think that's what you said.

2218
02:54:57,992 --> 02:54:59,412
It wasn't going in the right direction.

2219
02:54:59,532 --> 02:55:00,972
So you had to bring in somebody new.

2220
02:55:01,352 --> 02:55:03,713
That's okay for 19 kids that are there.

2221
02:55:04,193 --> 02:55:06,393
I believe between 11 administrators and teachers.

2222
02:55:07,334 --> 02:55:13,138
But you reward the fellow that's been there for 32 years with a $97,000 brand new job up at the high school.

2223
02:55:14,178 --> 02:55:15,119
To me, that's not right.

2224
02:55:15,419 --> 02:55:16,280
I don't think that's fair.

2225
02:55:16,320 --> 02:55:23,264
That's $97,000 that could have gone toward education, to a teacher, to books, to materials that teachers probably need.

2226
02:55:23,945 --> 02:55:27,247
Maybe you have a difference of opinion with the superintendent, but I wouldn't have done that.

2227
02:55:27,767 --> 02:55:29,368
I look at it an entirely different way.

2228
02:55:29,929 --> 02:55:34,292
I also look at the fact that when these new school buildings were built, there was a 5% annual

2229
02:55:37,114 --> 02:55:39,055
supposed to be in there for each particular budget.

2230
02:55:39,135 --> 02:55:53,039
Now, Councilor Caviello, I believe it was three years ago going into his first year, produced a document, not from him, but the school department that showed $1,203,000 of repairs that were needed in that school.

2231
02:55:54,159 --> 02:55:59,180
The reason why the schools got themselves in trouble in the first place was because they never kept maintenance up.

2232
02:55:59,921 --> 02:56:02,881
And at the rate we're going, we're going to find ourselves in the same situation.

2233
02:56:03,762 --> 02:56:05,082
All I ask for each school,

2234
02:56:05,492 --> 02:56:14,899
to be broken down individually to have a 5% inclusion of each school rather than all the schools together and try to figure out how this thing is going to work.

2235
02:56:15,739 --> 02:56:28,949
And the other part for which I, again, disagree with my superintendent, and I consider him to be my friend, but we have a difference of opinion, I just think the entrance to Meffitt High School does not present itself very good for an educational purpose.

2236
02:56:29,549 --> 02:56:34,653
If I'm bringing my child up there from the eighth grade going into the ninth, and I look at that front entrance of that building,

2237
02:56:35,070 --> 02:56:37,792
And I'm not going to accept the fact that it was a poor winter.

2238
02:56:37,992 --> 02:56:43,235
It's been like that for a while, with bricks that are broken, door handles that are off the thing.

2239
02:56:43,515 --> 02:56:45,737
And you walk into the, it's not very welcoming.

2240
02:56:46,517 --> 02:56:50,900
Medford High has a huge talent pool of students and teachers.

2241
02:56:51,620 --> 02:56:54,282
It gives a good education to the people in this community.

2242
02:56:54,962 --> 02:57:00,526
But of all the schools that Medford has, that high school gets the bad rap for its appearance.

2243
02:57:01,206 --> 02:57:04,228
And as we all know, an appearance can tell a huge story.

2244
02:57:05,657 --> 02:57:22,886
I just don't think right now, the way this budget's been presented, and knowing and seeing these department heads tell their particular stories, I don't feel that we're really getting what you call an accurate budget, especially since we just went two weeks ago to have over $1,200,000 in transfers from one department to another.

2245
02:57:23,727 --> 02:57:24,807
Are some transfers needed?

2246
02:57:24,967 --> 02:57:25,508
Absolutely.

2247
02:57:25,548 --> 02:57:26,288
No question about it.

2248
02:57:27,109 --> 02:57:29,390
But when one, two, three, four,

2249
02:57:29,974 --> 02:57:36,836
five department heads come in there and tell you that they couldn't put in their budget what they really wanted so we as counselors could understand it.

2250
02:57:37,376 --> 02:57:48,279
Maybe we wouldn't have accepted any of them, but all we've asked for for the past many years is show us what your wish list is, tell us how much it's going to cost, and maybe explain to us how you think we can fund it.

2251
02:57:49,159 --> 02:57:55,081
But when your predecessor tells them not to put it in there and they don't put it in there, that to me is wrong.

2252
02:57:55,821 --> 02:57:59,002
And because of that, I'm having a hard time right now telling you

2253
02:57:59,530 --> 02:58:06,295
You know, Louise, whether I'm going to vote for this budget tonight or not, because I don't think it reflects an accurate presentation of what department heads need.

2254
02:58:06,675 --> 02:58:11,499
I don't see anything coming back here that says the electrical department's going to get its $40,000.

2255
02:58:12,520 --> 02:58:20,005
So every single employee has its own phone rather than one phone for four people, and a table to work on, and a file cabinet to store things.

2256
02:58:20,906 --> 02:58:21,166
Okay?

2257
02:58:21,266 --> 02:58:21,907
That's number one.

2258
02:58:22,507 --> 02:58:27,671
I don't see anything in the electrical department that makes me feel satisfied that that one circle is going to be safe.

2259
02:58:28,165 --> 02:58:32,446
All I'm getting is a report back that somebody's accepting somebody else's opinion.

2260
02:58:32,846 --> 02:58:36,046
Well, that opinion isn't good enough for me when public safety is at issue.

2261
02:58:36,566 --> 02:58:55,430
When I hear a librarian tell me that for four years he's been stifled from putting in what he wants, and you hear the people from this community who brought the charge back, which forced Amir to automatically, mysteriously find $250,000 from a construction job, when we're sitting on $6.5 million in free cash,

2262
02:58:57,580 --> 02:58:58,700
I have a problem with that.

2263
02:58:59,460 --> 02:59:06,002
And when Paul Moki from the building department tells me all he needs is about 30, 40,000 to upgrade his department to computerize it, that's great.

2264
02:59:06,882 --> 02:59:07,702
But we didn't hear that.

2265
02:59:08,042 --> 02:59:19,605
And when I hear our chief of police tell me as of the morning of the date of the budget, that's the first time you and prior to you, your predecessor never had the opportunity or being invited to talk about these things.

2266
02:59:19,905 --> 02:59:24,406
That's bothers me because I think a lot of the times through the past, this council was led to believe,

2267
02:59:24,914 --> 02:59:31,457
When the budget was presented, okay, all the department heads agreed upon it, and maybe we should have asked more detailed questions.

2268
02:59:32,297 --> 02:59:34,018
But this year's budget was very enlightening.

2269
02:59:34,738 --> 02:59:51,705
So enlightening to the point that I honestly feel that what you were given for a budget to serve is not a true and honest and accurate budget, because if you're transferring a million dollars at the end of the year, as we've had for so many years in the past, and you just keep adding to your free cash, there is something wrong.

2270
02:59:52,275 --> 02:59:55,456
I'm not worried about the bond rating of our community right now.

2271
02:59:55,696 --> 03:00:01,938
What I'm worried about is how the taxpayers are going to be continuously taxed and taxed and taxed.

2272
03:00:02,438 --> 03:00:03,838
And I'll just leave you with this one thought.

2273
03:00:04,598 --> 03:00:07,179
We have so much development taking place in this community.

2274
03:00:07,639 --> 03:00:21,123
We were told that when in Wellington Circle, when stations landing in there, that was going to be such a boom to the city of Medford and to the taxpayers of this community, we would probably not be looking at a tax rate increase maybe for a few years.

2275
03:00:21,634 --> 03:00:27,358
We've had so much development since then, and again, we are taxed and taxed, increase, increase.

2276
03:00:28,138 --> 03:00:32,141
So maybe development for the sake of development is not working in this community.

2277
03:00:32,701 --> 03:00:45,449
Public safety, public works, public accommodations, plowing, all municipal services being put on the backs of the taxpayers to accommodate all this development and their taxes are not going down.

2278
03:00:46,030 --> 03:00:48,772
So I thank you for taking on your new role.

2279
03:00:49,632 --> 03:00:50,913
I know it was thrust upon you.

2280
03:00:51,874 --> 03:00:55,415
But unfortunately, I can't buy what's in front of me right now.

2281
03:00:55,555 --> 03:00:56,495
That's just my opinion.

2282
03:00:59,996 --> 03:01:15,160
Mr. President, if I may, I just want to say that in terms of looking at the budget, I think the council should feel comfortable that this budget is providing level services for all the departments.

2283
03:01:15,200 --> 03:01:20,642
So you will be getting the same level of services that you are getting in the city right now today.

2284
03:01:21,459 --> 03:01:23,661
There are a few additions to the budget.

2285
03:01:24,321 --> 03:01:29,025
The library budget was increased and that was increased out of new growth.

2286
03:01:29,886 --> 03:01:43,477
It truly was based upon certain building permits that were brought into the city and the assessor looking at what new growth could be and would be generated in the coming year.

2287
03:01:44,338 --> 03:01:49,362
One of the concerns with some of the wish list items is that they are one time

2288
03:01:51,711 --> 03:01:57,214
or they would add a substantial amount of expense to the budget.

2289
03:01:57,414 --> 03:02:02,276
And in order to cover those types of recurring expenses, we do need recurring revenue.

2290
03:02:03,037 --> 03:02:09,040
So when we look at free cash, it really can only be used for non-recurring expenses, those one-time expenses.

2291
03:02:09,060 --> 03:02:19,285
It can't really be used to fund the recurring expenses of the budget, or next year we will end up behind the eight ball before we even start.

2292
03:02:20,265 --> 03:02:43,439
So from where I stand and having been here for a number of weeks, now I think maybe six, eight weeks, I do think that the budget is a level service budget that will provide the citizens of Medford with at least in almost every department the same level of services and enhanced services in some of the other departments.

2293
03:02:44,080 --> 03:02:49,163
And the other one, in addition to the library, the other budget that was substantially increased was the fire department budget.

2294
03:02:49,890 --> 03:03:00,594
where there had been a, I believe they called it a safer grant, that had funded a certain number of firefighters who then had to be absorbed into the budget this year.

2295
03:03:00,974 --> 03:03:06,316
And that is where most of the new growth was directed to, the funding of those firefighter positions.

2296
03:03:06,356 --> 03:03:11,178
So I hope that that answers and alleviates some of the concerns of the council.

2297
03:03:12,138 --> 03:03:12,438
Thank you.

2298
03:03:12,518 --> 03:03:13,198
Councilor Knight.

2299
03:03:13,218 --> 03:03:15,819
You had that on from before, Mr. President.

2300
03:03:15,879 --> 03:03:17,160
My apologies, Councilor.

2301
03:03:17,180 --> 03:03:17,920
Councilor Camuso.

2302
03:03:19,081 --> 03:03:27,546
Thank you, Mr. President, and I want to thank you as well as Mayor McGlynn as he presents his final budget to the Medford City Council.

2303
03:03:28,587 --> 03:03:36,812
Once again, this is a budget that is going to provide city services at a level that I think is sufficient.

2304
03:03:36,832 --> 03:03:43,676
I've been a member of this council when times were really, really tough and when times were really, really good.

2305
03:03:44,376 --> 03:03:46,858
Right now, we're basically at a point or a juncture that

2306
03:03:48,069 --> 03:03:49,770
Things in the city are moving forward.

2307
03:03:50,571 --> 03:04:05,480
And I'm proud to say that that was a collaborative effort, Mayor McGlynn and the city council, the school committee, the superintendent, and all the magnificent department heads and employees that we have here in this very building.

2308
03:04:06,741 --> 03:04:14,306
But as I get ready to vote on Mayor McGlynn's final budget favorably, and I'm only one of seven members,

2309
03:04:15,818 --> 03:04:19,180
One thing that did stick out to me was the statistics on the parking program.

2310
03:04:19,960 --> 03:04:29,885
And it looks roughly about there's about 34 to 33,000 transactions at the meters throughout our community a month.

2311
03:04:30,885 --> 03:04:35,388
And that's a pretty impressive number.

2312
03:04:36,008 --> 03:04:42,211
And when you go to look at the citations and the citations collected, the number seems to be going down in the last few months.

2313
03:04:43,298 --> 03:04:52,011
And I think that's another interesting piece of data that we were presented from Mayor McGlynn and his staff.

2314
03:04:53,997 --> 03:04:56,678
With that being said, this is a good solid budget.

2315
03:04:57,899 --> 03:05:07,843
I'm very, very happy that the mayor agreed with this honorable body and funded the substance abuse prevention coordinator for the city of Medford.

2316
03:05:08,303 --> 03:05:12,604
I think it's a position that is much needed.

2317
03:05:12,624 --> 03:05:21,488
I think everyone on this council supported it when I first brought the idea forward and the mayor took it to one

2318
03:05:22,523 --> 03:05:25,365
One step further, another level, and he made it a full-time position.

2319
03:05:26,006 --> 03:05:43,880
So certainly, I'm proud of that, and I think that that's a legacy on this entire council, because we initiated it here, and hopefully it's going to be a position that turns out to be a lifesaver when people are ready to utilize the person that's awarded that job in the very near future.

2320
03:05:45,901 --> 03:05:49,965
But with that being said, I think the school department budget is a very solid budget, too.

2321
03:05:50,345 --> 03:05:51,646
The superintendent pointed out

2322
03:05:52,830 --> 03:05:56,692
the money that's being spent in maintenance and in repairs.

2323
03:05:57,453 --> 03:06:17,322
The superintendent also pointed out that the lump sum checks or the lump sum raises that some were saying were $60,000, a significant amount of money, were actually bonafide employment opportunities where people took new positions, is that correct, superintendent, that were publicly posted and things of that nature.

2324
03:06:19,397 --> 03:06:31,145
So just to clear up some of the confusion on that, because I get some phone calls from people in the school department saying, where did these jobs that are referred to on TV, where are they?

2325
03:06:31,905 --> 03:06:37,268
And so I'm thankful the superintendent gave us that in-depth report as well.

2326
03:06:37,729 --> 03:06:41,471
But like I said, I think that this is a solid budget, Mr. President.

2327
03:06:41,911 --> 03:06:44,573
I was prepared to vote on this budget last week.

2328
03:06:47,120 --> 03:06:48,762
after the final budget deliberations.

2329
03:06:49,382 --> 03:06:55,927
But, Louise, you did a fabulous job on your first budget, your first of many budgets, hopefully, here.

2330
03:06:56,528 --> 03:07:02,552
Either that or you'll be doing purchasing, I guess, because you have your contract as our purchasing agent for the next several years.

2331
03:07:03,113 --> 03:07:14,762
But, like I said, we're at a juncture in our community right now, Mr. President, where we're, in a very short period of time, the faces and names of

2332
03:07:16,236 --> 03:07:19,659
A lot of elected officials in this community are going to be changing.

2333
03:07:19,679 --> 03:07:21,220
That's factual at this point.

2334
03:07:21,820 --> 03:07:29,326
And it's really a good opportunity to keep the city stagnant and moving backwards or forward or wherever the voters may see fit.

2335
03:07:29,986 --> 03:07:34,309
And with that being said, I think that this is a solid, solid budget.

2336
03:07:34,910 --> 03:07:35,951
And I support it.

2337
03:07:36,151 --> 03:07:38,753
And hopefully it gets voted on favorably.

2338
03:07:39,293 --> 03:07:45,898
And the personnel throughout the community can get back to work tomorrow knowing that the budget is in place.

2339
03:07:46,809 --> 03:07:50,030
And I really don't have anything else to say about it.

2340
03:07:50,090 --> 03:07:56,733
But I want to thank the department heads, and particularly Louise Miller, Superintendent Belson, and Mayor McGlynn.

2341
03:07:57,653 --> 03:08:04,616
You know, he's been around, and this isn't a Mayor McGlynn, Ra-Ra speech at all, but he's been around when times were tough around here and when times were good.

2342
03:08:06,236 --> 03:08:10,458
And the city services were always a priority.

2343
03:08:11,598 --> 03:08:13,259
And the city services, where they are,

2344
03:08:14,520 --> 03:08:19,242
28 years ago and a lot added and not cut back.

2345
03:08:19,942 --> 03:08:26,205
So for that, and it was really good to always support a budget too with no trash fee.

2346
03:08:26,925 --> 03:08:30,707
Like our neighboring community of Malden, we were still able to get through another budget cycle without that.

2347
03:08:31,407 --> 03:08:38,490
So there's a lot of positive stuff happened over the past couple of years under Mayor McGlynn's watchful eye.

2348
03:08:39,771 --> 03:08:40,651
Thank you, Councillor.

2349
03:08:41,652 --> 03:08:42,372
Councillor Marks.

2350
03:08:43,780 --> 03:08:44,660
Thank you, Mr. President.

2351
03:08:44,881 --> 03:08:51,743
And, you know, as one member of the council, I'm glad we waited the one week to get responses.

2352
03:08:52,283 --> 03:09:05,388
We did get a lot of responses in the last week to questions that we've asked during the countless hours we had with the budget director and also the department heads.

2353
03:09:06,088 --> 03:09:09,149
And I think it was only appropriate that we took the time to make sure

2354
03:09:10,170 --> 03:09:15,275
that every single question was answered, so I'm grateful for that, and I'm grateful to all the responses.

2355
03:09:16,015 --> 03:09:18,057
You know, I see it a little different.

2356
03:09:18,077 --> 03:09:28,526
You know, when you hear words like, we're gonna provide the same level of service we did last year, I don't know how that's supposed to give you a warm, fuzzy feeling.

2357
03:09:30,028 --> 03:09:31,989
We're gonna do what we did for you last year.

2358
03:09:32,209 --> 03:09:36,113
We're not gonna improve, we're not gonna advance, we're gonna do what we did for you last year.

2359
03:09:37,156 --> 03:09:41,679
We're going to charge you more taxes but provide you the same services we did you last year.

2360
03:09:42,920 --> 03:09:46,202
And then when you look at the service, we talked about the Office of Community Development.

2361
03:09:46,423 --> 03:09:50,666
We've talked about that office for 10 years now under this administration.

2362
03:09:51,166 --> 03:09:51,826
Ten years.

2363
03:09:52,187 --> 03:09:55,149
They have one and a half person in that office.

2364
03:09:56,410 --> 03:09:59,232
We talked to the director of community development.

2365
03:09:59,532 --> 03:10:01,914
It was one of the first times she actually opened up to us.

2366
03:10:02,534 --> 03:10:04,175
And we asked her, what are your needs?

2367
03:10:04,215 --> 03:10:06,517
I believe it was Councilor Penta that asked, what are your needs?

2368
03:10:06,960 --> 03:10:17,091
And she said, you know what, in order to revitalize the square and do what we need, our office needs to do to move the city forward, it'd be nice to have a transportation planner.

2369
03:10:17,872 --> 03:10:19,574
It'd be nice to have a community planner.

2370
03:10:20,034 --> 03:10:21,596
It would be nice to have a grant writer.

2371
03:10:22,817 --> 03:10:27,222
Those are the few things that are a staple in an office of community development.

2372
03:10:28,111 --> 03:10:34,872
in order to look at revitalization and attract new business and new growth and new spending in our community.

2373
03:10:35,253 --> 03:10:36,113
That's what's needed.

2374
03:10:36,493 --> 03:10:39,173
This budget does not accomplish any of that.

2375
03:10:39,914 --> 03:10:43,474
So to sit here and say we're moving forward, where are we moving forward?

2376
03:10:44,274 --> 03:10:47,615
Same level of service we're hearing, same departments.

2377
03:10:48,375 --> 03:10:51,916
Yeah, have they sprinkled a few things here and there by osmosis?

2378
03:10:51,996 --> 03:10:53,876
Yes, something's bound to happen.

2379
03:10:54,797 --> 03:10:56,217
But other than that, really,

2380
03:10:56,748 --> 03:11:06,812
You know, we talked about a 311 system, a way residents can electronically report concerns for city services.

2381
03:11:08,373 --> 03:11:12,895
We have yet, Somerville has it, Malden has it, Boston has it, Cambridge has it.

2382
03:11:13,215 --> 03:11:21,218
We as a city have yet to implement any logical way residents can submit a service request in our community.

2383
03:11:21,773 --> 03:11:27,654
And it also helps the administration during budget time when you're able to take all these requests and say, you know what?

2384
03:11:28,034 --> 03:11:32,195
We had 3,000 requests for forestry and only 50 requests for parks.

2385
03:11:32,716 --> 03:11:38,077
Let's take the budget and let's increase our budget for forestry based on the requests we're receiving.

2386
03:11:38,457 --> 03:11:40,657
There's no tracking mechanism in this community.

2387
03:11:41,898 --> 03:11:43,318
Honestly, I don't know how it operates.

2388
03:11:43,678 --> 03:11:51,140
And we're going to find out come January how this city operates, because it's been a lot of smoke and mirrors for many years in this community.

2389
03:11:51,813 --> 03:11:53,194
The 311 system works.

2390
03:11:54,154 --> 03:11:58,756
It works in every other community, but except Method can't find the time.

2391
03:11:59,316 --> 03:12:03,438
I don't know if we don't have the brainpower to implement it, or we don't have the will to do it.

2392
03:12:03,898 --> 03:12:04,638
I don't know what it is.

2393
03:12:05,258 --> 03:12:08,940
But every resident suffers because we don't have 311 in this community.

2394
03:12:09,560 --> 03:12:11,621
You know, we talked about the engineering department.

2395
03:12:12,741 --> 03:12:19,304
The engineering director came up, and she mentioned that they don't have data collection software.

2396
03:12:19,644 --> 03:12:21,345
They have files and files of

2397
03:12:22,064 --> 03:12:25,867
of data that's not electronic.

2398
03:12:25,907 --> 03:12:28,249
They can't find what's in these cabinets.

2399
03:12:28,549 --> 03:12:37,195
I believe she said it was about $30,000 to implement a system where they can have a tracking mechanism for all the electronic documents they have.

2400
03:12:37,655 --> 03:12:41,158
That's a small fee in a $150 million budget.

2401
03:12:42,519 --> 03:12:45,621
As was mentioned earlier, there's one phone for four employees.

2402
03:12:45,641 --> 03:12:49,704
And forget about voicemail.

2403
03:12:49,744 --> 03:12:50,865
The mayor's against voicemail.

2404
03:12:51,421 --> 03:12:53,662
That's how progressive we are in this community.

2405
03:12:54,003 --> 03:12:55,604
He's against voicemail.

2406
03:12:56,004 --> 03:12:59,306
They're still using drafting tables as desk.

2407
03:12:59,326 --> 03:13:02,308
How would you like to write on a drafting table all day?

2408
03:13:03,729 --> 03:13:04,830
It doesn't make any sense.

2409
03:13:05,430 --> 03:13:11,134
But these are the small requests that for some reason we can't get a handle on in this community.

2410
03:13:11,874 --> 03:13:19,279
You know, during the budget, um, we had the council on aging in and I offered a motion to the budget because of

2411
03:13:20,335 --> 03:13:36,205
the involvement I see at the senior center across the street, we were told that there were 24,796 sign-ins by seniors for programming activities at the senior center.

2412
03:13:36,645 --> 03:13:43,409
It ranged from bingo, to dinner movie, to Zumba, to chair yoga, and the list goes on and on and on.

2413
03:13:44,129 --> 03:13:46,991
They only receive state funding for their programs.

2414
03:13:47,672 --> 03:13:54,677
We asked that we set up, similar to what we did for the art community, $5,000 to provide for additional programming.

2415
03:13:56,278 --> 03:13:58,480
The director told us she could use it.

2416
03:13:59,000 --> 03:14:05,365
Then we were told, well, they also wanted the Council on Aging gave back money, transferred back money to the city.

2417
03:14:05,765 --> 03:14:16,213
I don't know, when I'm talking to a department head face to face, and they tell me $5,000 can go a long way for senior programming in the city, I tend to trust the department head.

2418
03:14:17,658 --> 03:14:20,099
I tend to trust the department could use that money.

2419
03:14:20,579 --> 03:14:29,542
And I think it's a shame that we got a response back that the mayor will take that under advisement in a program that's so utilized by thousands of seniors in this community.

2420
03:14:30,623 --> 03:14:34,164
You know, we heard from the chief of police.

2421
03:14:35,585 --> 03:14:39,026
This budget does not contain any money for new police vehicles.

2422
03:14:40,878 --> 03:14:44,701
Although we have vehicles that have 250,000 miles.

2423
03:14:45,101 --> 03:14:48,744
These vehicles operate seven days a week, 24 hours a day.

2424
03:14:49,104 --> 03:14:56,030
Try running your vehicle seven days a week, 24 hours a day with multiple drivers and see what happens to your vehicle.

2425
03:14:57,191 --> 03:14:58,051
They don't last long.

2426
03:14:59,653 --> 03:15:04,436
The chief asked for six marked vehicles and six unmarked vehicles.

2427
03:15:04,997 --> 03:15:07,679
That is not going to be part of this year's budget.

2428
03:15:08,039 --> 03:15:10,061
So I don't know how excited I'd be

2429
03:15:10,483 --> 03:15:11,303
about this budget.

2430
03:15:11,663 --> 03:15:16,404
It doesn't include the very fabric of a community, which is public safety.

2431
03:15:17,645 --> 03:15:18,185
Vehicles.

2432
03:15:18,625 --> 03:15:20,185
You can have as many officers as you want.

2433
03:15:20,425 --> 03:15:24,306
If you don't have the vehicle to take them to a scene or answer a call, then what good is it?

2434
03:15:25,426 --> 03:15:27,307
Talk to the men and women in the police department.

2435
03:15:27,587 --> 03:15:28,887
They'll tell you about the vehicles.

2436
03:15:29,207 --> 03:15:30,808
Take a ride in the cars.

2437
03:15:31,048 --> 03:15:32,608
I challenge you to take a ride in the cars.

2438
03:15:33,628 --> 03:15:36,249
They're smelling exhaust fumes from some of these vehicles.

2439
03:15:39,462 --> 03:15:42,183
Then we heard from the chief of the fire department.

2440
03:15:42,564 --> 03:15:44,765
He asked for $2 million in station repairs.

2441
03:15:45,966 --> 03:15:53,910
We still can't get a repair list of what's needed from the last repairs that were done with that bonding money that Councilor Wongo just mentioned.

2442
03:15:56,191 --> 03:16:08,338
You know, it seems to me when you're talking about level services and complimenting the fact that level services are good news,

2443
03:16:09,115 --> 03:16:13,096
then it seems to me the status quo is what's prevailing in the city.

2444
03:16:14,556 --> 03:16:16,316
And that's what's taking place in this community.

2445
03:16:17,476 --> 03:16:19,697
It seems to me the status quo is fine.

2446
03:16:20,277 --> 03:16:21,857
Hey, look, we're doing what we did last year.

2447
03:16:22,877 --> 03:16:24,258
That's unacceptable in my opinion.

2448
03:16:25,138 --> 03:16:27,078
And, you know, there are a lot of positive things.

2449
03:16:27,098 --> 03:16:31,179
We heard from the superintendent of schools, and a lot of positive things are going in there.

2450
03:16:31,859 --> 03:16:38,020
As a former graduate of the vocational school, I'm happy with the direction Heidi Riccio's taking the vocational school.

2451
03:16:38,373 --> 03:16:52,684
They're adding a lot of program offerings to the vocational school, state-of-the-art offerings, which will attract kids back from Lexington Minuteman, which is costing us hundreds of thousands of dollars to send these outside placements.

2452
03:16:53,385 --> 03:16:56,828
We're adding textbooks in the social studies department.

2453
03:16:57,148 --> 03:16:59,370
Our guidance department added an additional counselor.

2454
03:17:00,050 --> 03:17:04,113
We're looking at additional desk and chairs throughout the elementary schools.

2455
03:17:04,914 --> 03:17:06,275
As Councilor Camuso mentioned,

2456
03:17:06,898 --> 03:17:10,481
The city is providing a prevention outreach program coordinator.

2457
03:17:11,341 --> 03:17:15,804
We recently put on a code enforcement officer that Councilor Caviello has been talking about.

2458
03:17:16,645 --> 03:17:18,486
So there are positive things happening.

2459
03:17:19,147 --> 03:17:25,531
I just don't think it's enough to outweigh the current status quo in the way this city is operating, to be quite honest with you.

2460
03:17:26,312 --> 03:17:28,954
I am appreciative of everything that was sent from the administration.

2461
03:17:29,354 --> 03:17:32,837
I think this budget process overall went rather smooth.

2462
03:17:33,417 --> 03:17:34,778
We got our budget packages.

2463
03:17:35,568 --> 03:17:43,212
well ahead of time, so it gave us ample opportunity to view them, which has always been a bone of contention with me and I know members of this council.

2464
03:17:44,413 --> 03:17:58,480
I will support the budget here tonight, but I'm hoping going forward that the status quo and the fact that we're going to provide level services is no longer bragging right in this city.

2465
03:17:58,900 --> 03:18:00,661
And it should be something we frown upon.

2466
03:18:01,441 --> 03:18:04,703
And I think it's a sad commentary when we have to say,

2467
03:18:05,083 --> 03:18:13,208
we're providing the same services we did last year, knowing that in my opinion, a lot of those services are not accurate enough as is.

2468
03:18:14,008 --> 03:18:19,332
And I really think it's a sad commentary, but I will support this budget here tonight.

2469
03:18:20,252 --> 03:18:31,099
And I look forward to next year's budget and the discussion and dialogue over how we can improve our community

2470
03:18:31,566 --> 03:18:48,553
have a vision of community development, look at some of the needs, infrastructure needs that we have, discussion on a new police department, discussion on revamping our old fire departments, and looking at the roads and the sidewalks and everything else.

2471
03:18:48,633 --> 03:18:49,633
The list goes on and on.

2472
03:18:49,893 --> 03:18:50,974
The public library.

2473
03:18:50,994 --> 03:18:55,456
These are the things that really I think we have to look at as a community.

2474
03:18:56,236 --> 03:18:58,997
And I look forward to those discussions next year.

2475
03:19:01,783 --> 03:19:02,904
Thank you, Councillor Marks.

2476
03:19:04,685 --> 03:19:05,566
Councillor Penter.

2477
03:19:07,087 --> 03:19:08,788
A couple of things pop out.

2478
03:19:09,689 --> 03:19:14,373
The issue on the kiosks in the square, citations have gone up.

2479
03:19:14,413 --> 03:19:15,193
They haven't gone down.

2480
03:19:15,233 --> 03:19:17,095
January was 590, February was 1,800, March was 2,393, April was 2,689.

2481
03:19:17,135 --> 03:19:21,038
Just in the month of May, it went down by some 300 citations, but they're still issuing over 2,000 of those a month.

2482
03:19:31,652 --> 03:19:32,453
That's an awful lot.

2483
03:19:32,673 --> 03:19:34,094
It's an awful lot of citations.

2484
03:19:34,734 --> 03:19:47,441
And as the chief has indicated, and I believe in his report back to us, that some 400 of the 1,100 citations that were appealed were either reduced or they were abated to some degree.

2485
03:19:48,782 --> 03:20:00,128
This kiosk program, as we all know, has been a handicap, in my opinion, to businesses throughout the community as it relates to not being business friendly,

2486
03:20:01,507 --> 03:20:09,129
when in fact we could have engaged in a revenue, I mean, strike that, a traffic enforcement program rather than a revenue enhancement program.

2487
03:20:10,029 --> 03:20:18,270
I hear what some of my colleagues are saying, but the hard part about supporting a budget like this is the following.

2488
03:20:18,791 --> 03:20:23,772
Louise, you were there because you presented this budget and worked on it with us.

2489
03:20:25,612 --> 03:20:29,173
Is there any reason why in the electrical department for their $40,000 that they were looking for,

2490
03:20:32,135 --> 03:20:51,922
not to strike the electrical engineering, the building department probably almost around the same amount, at least the police department, even if he got a couple or two or three cruises, you had a fight for the $5,000 and the Council of Aging budget, you had a fight to get the $227,000, and you added on to make it $250,000 for the library.

2491
03:20:52,903 --> 03:20:59,565
Is there any reason, since you knew that these were concerns from the Council, and before this came back tonight, that you couldn't have come back

2492
03:21:00,471 --> 03:21:06,615
and added this in the budget, and some shape me in a reform, because the budget did increase by $4,800,000 from last year.

2493
03:21:06,875 --> 03:21:10,497
This is almost two years in a row that this budget's increased by approximately $5 million.

2494
03:21:11,617 --> 03:21:14,159
So an increase in the budget by $5 million are close to it.

2495
03:21:14,819 --> 03:21:17,181
You're maxing out 2.5% to the max.

2496
03:21:18,722 --> 03:21:24,665
And as Councilor Marks just alluded to, what you're doing is, well, we don't want to see this next year.

2497
03:21:25,365 --> 03:21:28,107
But I've heard that rhetoric before about not seeing it next year.

2498
03:21:28,528 --> 03:21:30,609
I'm seeing it here right now for the first year.

2499
03:21:31,989 --> 03:21:34,670
And this is not to put it on you, because this is what was handed to you.

2500
03:21:36,151 --> 03:21:48,795
But if one, two, three, four, if five department heads are all saying the same thing, and even if you increased each one of these departments by $30,000 each, that's what, $150,000 that you can't find in the budget?

2501
03:21:48,835 --> 03:21:50,376
When, in fact, you just transferred over $1,200,000 at the end of the year?

2502
03:21:59,231 --> 03:22:00,912
I just don't buy into that.

2503
03:22:01,112 --> 03:22:15,755
And just what's happened, unfortunately, with the kiosks and the business people in the community and the last horror show of a lady yesterday with the kiosks and the machine and being yelled at when she went to Park Medford.

2504
03:22:16,475 --> 03:22:27,358
And tonight, getting a report back from someone who had to wait two months to get his appeal answered, when I thought the appeal was taking place in this building and Park Medford is still doing the appeals.

2505
03:22:28,029 --> 03:22:36,652
I don't know how this works, Chief, but if Park Medford is doing the appeals, when we were told it was being done in this building, there's still something wrong.

2506
03:22:36,672 --> 03:22:45,316
I just don't think I'm going to vote for this budget, because to me, it does not represent a budget that represents the quality of life that the people of this community need.

2507
03:22:45,596 --> 03:22:46,496
That's just my opinion.

2508
03:22:47,037 --> 03:22:51,999
I think I'm going to stick to it, because, like I said, this has been very insightful to me.

2509
03:22:55,603 --> 03:22:59,726
to talk to you and tell you things that we never heard before, that bothers me.

2510
03:23:00,547 --> 03:23:01,227
It bothers me.

2511
03:23:01,307 --> 03:23:02,288
And it should bother you, too.

2512
03:23:05,431 --> 03:23:07,112
If I may, Mr. President.

2513
03:23:07,172 --> 03:23:25,026
So with regard to the requests that were made by the department heads, the fire department and police department really had capital requests or large one-time expenditures, with the exception of the police cruisers, which

2514
03:23:26,910 --> 03:23:33,513
They're a substantial amount of money in order to start some type of replacement cycle with regard to the police cruisers.

2515
03:23:34,433 --> 03:23:42,976
With respect to the building department software, we need more information before we fund anything in the budget.

2516
03:23:43,696 --> 03:23:52,399
There has to be some research done into what type of software, how it would be implemented, and some type of implementation timeframe.

2517
03:23:53,731 --> 03:23:55,572
We don't have any of that information right now.

2518
03:23:55,912 --> 03:24:05,535
And the engineering department was, did have some funding available this year and was asked to get quotes on some of the items that were asked for.

2519
03:24:05,615 --> 03:24:12,177
Some of them will be able to be purchased and others, I believe the city engineer did respond.

2520
03:24:12,617 --> 03:24:20,840
She did not have prices with respect to the document management program, but for a small amount of money could get a study to figure out what

2521
03:24:21,480 --> 03:24:24,721
document management program her department would require.

2522
03:24:25,701 --> 03:24:28,002
And there is money available for that.

2523
03:24:28,022 --> 03:24:32,443
It was only to the order of $2,000 to get the study completed.

2524
03:24:32,883 --> 03:24:39,525
So all of, I mean, these items are items that certainly require further study.

2525
03:24:40,085 --> 03:24:46,847
But we're not right, I would say at this point, to put into this fiscal year 16 operating budget.

2526
03:24:46,887 --> 03:24:48,147
And the capital items can't be.

2527
03:24:49,050 --> 03:24:55,392
But in all fairness to you coming on late in the process, had these wish list issues been discussed?

2528
03:24:55,432 --> 03:24:58,833
Now, you just got through saying in the building department, you needed more info.

2529
03:24:59,333 --> 03:25:06,015
So if this was brought up in February, which I believe is when the building department, why would the questions asked then of him?

2530
03:25:06,095 --> 03:25:07,675
Why should he have to come up with it?

2531
03:25:08,375 --> 03:25:16,597
If he's telling you what he'd like to have, then isn't that what the budget director does or an assistant to the budget director going into the engineering department?

2532
03:25:16,878 --> 03:25:18,398
She's been asking for this for four years.

2533
03:25:19,401 --> 03:25:28,026
I can't answer for the prior budget director, and also I can't answer to any conversations that they had.

2534
03:25:28,627 --> 03:25:35,771
I can only answer the question, you know, today based upon what was said in the budget hearings after she was gone.

2535
03:25:35,931 --> 03:25:41,054
But when all these department heads indicated that they made the request and they were told not to include it and not to talk about it.

2536
03:25:42,375 --> 03:25:43,576
Point of information, Mr. President.

2537
03:25:43,596 --> 03:25:44,916
Point of information, Councilor Camuso.

2538
03:25:44,936 --> 03:25:49,079
These are all proposals that were brought

